"{\"uid\": \"nbcchicago.com-paris-2024-summer-olympics-unexpected-turn-of-events-sees-jordan-chiles-get-last-minute-score-change-in-floor-final-3512591\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles relinquished the crown in the women's gymnastics floor final on Monday, taking silver behind Brazil's Rebeca Andrade.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5513029962127481, \"rank\": 0.7949863422762222, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA's Jordan Chiles took bronze.\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 131, \"end\": 139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9993595920138655, \"rank\": 0.0005314801513628055, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 142, \"end\": 155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's gymnastics floor final at the2024 Olympicsended in dramatic fashion with U.S. star Jordan Chiles receiving an unexpected score shift that changed everything.\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 265, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition was over and it had appeared Chiles was out of medal contention, sitting in fifth place with a score of 13.666.\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stream NBC 5 for free, 24/7, wherever you are.\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But just as fans were expecting a podium celebration that would see Simone Biles,who scored a silver medal in the event,as the only American on it, Chiles was seen jumping in the air.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 586, \"end\": 598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was the first one to see ...\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was like jumping up and down,\\\" Chiles, who lost her voice while cheering and screaming, told reporters after the event.\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA hadsubmitted an inquiryon Chiles' score, which was then reviewed by the judges and, in an unexpected move, her score was adjusted.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 858, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9993595920138655, \"rank\": 0.0005314801513628055, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles now sat at 13.766 -- which was just barely enough to put her at bronze.\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So what changed exactly and how does it work?\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1124, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A gymnast can make a verbal challenge, called an inquiry, to the judges after their routine.\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The verbal inquiry must be followed by a written inquiry and can only occur after the gymnast's final score has been posted.\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scores can be raised, lowered or remain the same based on the inquiry.\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both were the case during the floor final at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Romania filed an inquiry for Sabrina Maneca-Voinea's score, but it remained unchanged.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1510, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Salerno\", \"score\": 0.7530356031553969, \"rank\": 0.3279584601443456, \"text\": \"Sabrina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Salerno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Salerno\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles - the last competitor of the day - initially received a 13.666 from judges.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After some delay, her total was boosted by 0.1 following an inquiry about her difficulty score.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The challenge involved her Tour Jete Full, one of the elements of her routine, which Team USA felt was not properly scored.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9993595920138655, \"rank\": 0.0005314801513628055, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles did not get credit for the move in both qualifications and the team final.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1956, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The judges agreed and the decision pushed Chiles past Romanians Ana Barbosu and Sabrina Maneca-Voinea and into third.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2012, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanians\", \"score\": 0.9996569679111615, \"rank\": 0.00033171524548545727, \"text\": \"Romanians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanians\"}, {\"begin\": 2038, \"end\": 2045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Salerno\", \"score\": 0.7530356031553969, \"rank\": 0.3279584601443456, \"text\": \"Sabrina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Salerno\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabrina_Salerno\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They had told me when they [filed the inquiry] and I was like, 'OK let us see what they come back with,'\\\" Chiles said.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she did not expect to see a big change.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I honestly did not expect this like whatsoever,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nine judges are chosen to score each Olympics gymnastics event.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those judges are broken into three groups: the D panel (difficulty score), E panel (execution score) and reference panel.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Difficulty score  The D panel is made up of two judges who determine the difficulty score.\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both judges record their difficulty score, accounting for the eight most difficult skills - including dismount - for women and 10 most difficult skills for men.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The D panel judges compare scores and determine the routine's difficulty score.\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Vault is the only apparatus that has a predetermined difficulty score, which is displayed to the judges before the gymnast begins their vault.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Execution score  The E panel has five judges who determine the execution score.\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 3048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The execution score starts at 10.0 and the E panel makes deductions for errors during the routine.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Deductions range in value from 0.1 to 1.0.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The five judges each record their own execution score for the routine.\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top and bottom scores are dropped and the three remaining scores are averaged out to determine a final execution score.\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Neutral deductions  Certain errors such as time violations, stepping out of bounds, behavior faults and falls are penalized as neutral deductions.\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Inquiries  A gymnast can make a verbal challenge, called an inquiry, to the judges after their routine.\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The verbal inquiry must be followed by a written inquiry and can only occur after the gymnast's final score has been posted.\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scores can be raised, lowered or remain the same based on the inquiry.\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 3836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Code of Points  The Code of Points defines the scoring system for each level of gymnastics competitions.Different gymnastics levels, disciplines and countries have their own codes.\", \"from\": 3838, \"to\": 4018, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheInternational Gymnastics Federationssets the Code of Points for the top level of the sport, including theParis Olympics.\", \"from\": 4019, \"to\": 4142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4036, \"end\": 4046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9987896898953565, \"rank\": 0.0012090749223977286, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each athlete is awarded both and execution and difficulty score following their routines.\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According toNBC Olympics,there is no more \\\"Perfect 10\\\" in gymnastics, but gymnasts can still reach a perfect score -- there is just no number associated with it.\", \"from\": 4235, \"to\": 4396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now, a perfect score for a gymnast would be receiving no deductions from the judges, while also completing their planned routine with full difficulty.\", \"from\": 4398, \"to\": 4549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the open-ended scoring system, no gymnast has received a perfect score,\\\" NBC Olympics reported.\", \"from\": 4550, \"to\": 4651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4629, \"end\": 4641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top eight gymnasts on each apparatus in qualifying advance to the respective apparatus final.\", \"from\": 4653, \"to\": 4750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No scores carry over from qualifying and the starting order for an apparatus final is determined by a random draw.\", \"from\": 4751, \"to\": 4865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each gymnast gets one attempt on an apparatus in the event final, with the exception of vault.\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 4961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnasts in the women's and men's vault finals must perform two different vaults from two different vault groups.\", \"from\": 4962, \"to\": 5075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The average score of the two vaults is then averaged out to give a final apparatus score.\", \"from\": 5076, \"to\": 5165, \"entities\": []}]}"